<title>USA: Tax to hurt United Water's Q3 by $0.35/shr.</title>
<headline>Tax to hurt United Water's Q3 by $0.35/shr.</headline>
<text>
<p>HARRINGTON PARK, N.J., July 17 - United Water Resources Inc Thursday said a one-time U.K. &quot;windfall profits&quot; tax to be imposed on privatized British utilities will hurt its third quarter earnings by about $0.35 a share.</p>
<p>Chief executive Donald Correll added the tax, imposed on its investment in U.K. water services company Northumbrian Water Group Plc, will not affect its cash flow or its ability to pay dividends.</p>
<p>Correll said United Water factored in and considered the possible imposition of the tax when it invested in Northumbrian.</p>
</text>
